Studies in Texas and Louisiana marshes have demonstrated that production is related to temperature, salinity, and access to emergent marsh vegetation.  We are currently developing a systems model that will simulate recruitment, growth, and emigration of brown shrimp. This data will be used to help validate the model</abstract>          <purpose>The goal of this study is to examine the effects of differing temperature, salinity, and marsh surface flooding regimes on brown shrimp growth and mortality rates</purpose>          <supplinf/>       </descript>       <timeperd>          <timeinfo>             <rngdates>                <begdate>20110406</begdate>                <enddate>20110815</enddate>             </rngdates>          </timeinfo>          <current/>       </timeperd>       <status>          <progress>                                 In work                             </progress>          <update>As needed</update>       </status>       <spdom><!-- descgeog: Four shallow marsh ponds.
